cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of joint caching and resource allocation in a network of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) that service wireless ground users over the LTE licensed and unlicensed (LTE-U) bands. The paper proposes a distributed algorithm based on the machine learning framework of liquid state machine (LSM) to solve this problem. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category. The paper also deals with spectrum allocation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper proposes a distributed algorithm for resource allocation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves caching of contents, which falls under the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
